3. # const (The Locked, Permanent Box)
   const is short for constant.
   Use this by default for everything unless you know for sure
   the value must change later.Unchangeable: Once you assign a value,
   it is locked. You cannot reassign it to something else.Must Initialize:
   You cannot leave it empty; you must give it a value right away when you create it.Strict Scope: Just like let, it is block-scoped and stays locked inside its curly braces {}.

   # SYNTAX OF CONST
   const pi = 3.14;
   pi = 5; // ERROR! You cannot change a constant box.
